downregulated in the CR+ isolate. Many genes mediating acid resistance and 
colanic acid biosynthesis, which influence biofilm formation directly or 
indirectly, were also down-regulated. Comparative genomics of CR+ and CR- 
isolates revealed the presence of a short duplicated sequence in the rcsB gene 
of the CR+ isolate. The alignment of the amino acid sequences of RcsB of the two 
isolates showed truncation of RcsB in the CR+ isolate at the insertion site of 
the duplicated sequence. Complementation of CR+ isolate with rcsB of the CR- 
parent restored parental phenotypes to the CR+ isolate.
