affecting bacterial survival in growth-restrictive environments through 
upregulation of genes promoting biofilm formation while downregulating certain 
metabolic functions. Understanding whether rcsB inactivation enhances 
persistence and survival of O157 in carrier animals and the environment would be 
important in developing strategies for controlling this bacterial pathogen in 
these niches.

