increases the cellular Fe quota. In vitro and in vivo protein-DNA binding assays 
revealed that the elevated intracellular Fe poisons the primary Cu 
detoxification transcription regulator CueR, resulting in dysregulation of its 
target genes copA and cueO and activation of the secondary Cu detoxification 
