coincides with copper transfer as monitored by electron paramagnetic resonance 
spectroscopy. These experiments establish a role for CueP within the copper 
supply pathway for Salmonella Cu,Zn-SodCII. Copper binding by CueP in this 
pathogen may confer protection of the periplasm from copper-mediated damage 
while sustaining vital cupro-enzyme activity.

