highest concentration and affinity for the core RNA polymerase. The E. coli 
protein Rsd is regarded as an anti-sigma factor, inhibiting σ(70)-dependent 
transcription at the onset of stationary growth. Although binding of Rsd to 
σ(70) has been shown and numerous structural studies on Rsd have been performed 
the detailed mechanism of action is still unknown.
