structure, presumably in the hinge region. The partially unfolded form of the 
gene-3-protein is metastable, and trans-Pro213 arrests the protein in this 
activated form for an extended time, long enough to find the receptor TolA. The 
partial unfolding and its timing by prolyl isomerization are essential for the 
biological function.

