interact with the TolA receptor at the cell surface. The refolding of the N1-N2 
fragment begins with the folding of domain N1, which takes a few milliseconds, 
followed by the folding of domain N2, which is complete within five minutes. The 
subsequent domain assembly is unusually slow and shows a time-constant of 6200 s 
at 25 degrees C. We found that the rate of this reaction is controlled by the 
trans to cis isomerization of the Gln212-Pro213 bond in the hinge subdomain of 
