gene-3-protein. The substitution of Pro213 by Gly accelerated domain association 
30-fold and revealed that the folding of the two individual domains and their 
assembly are indeed sequential steps in the refolding of the gene-3-protein. In 
the course of infection, the domains must separate to expose the binding site 
for TolA on domain N1. The kinetic block of domain reassembly caused by Pro213 
isomerization could ensure that after the initial binding of N2 to the F pilus 
the open state persists until N1 and TolA are close enough for their mutual 
interaction. Pro213 isomerization might thus serve as a slow conformational 
