NlaIV modification and restriction genes are homologues of the leuD and leuB 
genes of enteric bacteria, which code for enzymes in the leucine biosynthesis 
pathway. This gene context implies a possible new mode of gene regulation for 
the RM.NlaIV system, which would involve a mechanism similar to the recently 
discovered leucine/Lrp regulon in E. coli.

