Drug efflux systems play a major role in resistance to a wide range of noxious 
compounds in several Gram negative species. Here, we report the drug resistance 
and virulence phenotypes of Salmonella mutants defective in either 
resistance-nodulation-division (RND)-type systems and/or in drug efflux systems 
belonging to the major facilitator (MFS), multidrug and toxic compound extrusion 
