An iTRAQ-based comparative and quantitative proteomics analysis of a soil-borne 
Mn(II)-oxidizing bacterium, Escherichia coli MB266, was conducted during the 
exponential and stationary growth phases. A total of 1850 proteins were 
identified in 4 samples, of which 373 and 456 proteins were significantly up- or 
down-regulated in at least one pairwise comparison, respectively. The iTRAQ data 
