In Bradyrhizobium japonicum, the N2-fixing root nodule endosymbiont of soybean, 
a group of genes required for microaerobic, anaerobic, or symbiotic growth is 
controlled by FixK2, a key regulator that is part of the FixLJ-FixK2 cascade. 
