premature transcription termination at the leader terminator. Footprint and 
toeprint experiments support a regulatory model involving molecular mimicry 
between the L20-binding sites on 23S rRNA and the mRNA. Our data suggest that 
Nomura's model of ribosomal protein biosynthesis based on autogenous control and 
molecular mimicry is also valid in Gram-positive organisms.

