of whether it was grown on agar or in liquid medium. The exopolysaccharide was 
isolated from the liquid growth medium of ΔwaaF cells, hydrolyzed, and analyzed 
by high-performance liquid chromatography with an ion-exchange column, and the 
results indicated that the exopolysaccharide was consistent with colanic acid. 
