showed that the RcsB protein and an RcsAB box in the mat regulatory region, but 
not RcsC, RcsD, AckA, and Pta, are essential for initiation of mat 
transcription. Gel retardation assays showed that RcsB specifically binds to the 
mat promoter DNA, which enables its function in promoting biofilm formation by 
E. coli.

