implies that there are at least two different classes of IscR binding sites 
conserved among many bacteria. The findings presented here indicate a more 
general role of IscR in the regulation of Fe-S cluster biogenesis and that IscR 
contributes to the O(2) regulation of several promoters controlling the 
expression of anaerobic Fe-S proteins.

