A mutant of Escherichia coli strain CanR 22 has been isolated which is resistant 
to growth inhibition by canavanine, an analogue of arginine. The properties of 
this strain and of another canavanine-resistant mutant, JC182-5 (isolated by 
Celis et al. [5]), were studied. The mutation is pleiotropic in that it results 
