be transferred to the recipient Escherichia coli. WGS indicated that bla NDM-1 
genes were carried by diverse plasmids, including IncHI2/IncN, IncX3, and one 
unclassified plasmid type. The backbone structure of these plasmids is involved 
in replication initiation (repAB), partitioning (parABM), and conjugation/type 
IV secretion (tra/virB). Analysis of the genetic environment showed that bla 
NDM-1 in three plasmids exhibited a highly similar structure to protype Tn125. 
