H-NS and Fis proteins, as well as by the small signal molecule ppGpp and the 
initiating nucleotides. During amino acid starvation, the concentration of ppGpp 
increases, and binding of this alarmone to RNA polymerase (RNAP) leads to 
inhibition of rRNA transcription, a regulatory event called stringent response. 
