to the advantage provided by OmpC, we provide evidence that OmpC is important 
for E. coli to colonize the intestine because its smaller pore size excludes 
bile salts or other unknown toxic substances, while OmpF is deleterious because 
its larger pore size allows bile salts or other unknown toxic substances to 
