elucidation. Herein, we noted that curli fimbriae formation was inhibited by 
yccT-i.e., a gene that encodes a periplasmic protein of unknown function 
regulated by CsgD. Furthermore, curli fimbriae formation was strongly repressed 
by CsgD overexpression caused by a multicopy plasmid in BW25113-the 
non-cellulose-producing strain. YccT deficiency prevented these CsgD effects. 
