expression. These effects were addressed by deleting the N-terminal signal 
peptide of YccT. Localization, gene expression, and phenotypic analyses revealed 
that YccT-dependent inhibition of curli fimbriae formation and curli protein 
expression was mediated by the two-component regulatory system EnvZ/OmpR. 
