is consistent with those of spontaneously arising rifampicin-resistant mutants 
of E. coli and Mycobacterium tuberculosis at certain critical residues. This 
suggests that the natural resistance of B. burgdorferi to rifampicin may be due 
to the primary amino-acid sequence of its beta-subunit.

