each other; no interactions occurred between heterologous combinations of the P. 
aeruginosa proteins and between a P. aeruginosa FecI homolog and E. coli FecR. 
The results demonstrate that region 4 of FecI specifically binds FecR and that 
this binding is necessary for FecI to function as a sigma factor.

